                  </persName>
            , and Mr. Grange, all depos'd, That they were present when they were taken; that Ward confess'd the Fact, and directed them where they found Part of the Cistern; but as to Davis, who was taken in another Room in the same House, where he had got under the Bed, he did not confess the Fact, yet his hiding himself when the House was search'd, and the Cistern being too large and heavy to be conveniently brought away by Ward himself, the Jury were of Opinion that they were equally concerned, and according brought in their Verdict, that they were both <rs id="t17280605-7-verdict33" type="verdictDescription">
